# Practical Playbooks

Be able to write playbooks for:

- Ping all servers
- Install Apache/Nginx
- Install multiple packages
- Create users
- Create groups
- Copy files
- Generate configuration from templates
- Restart services using handlers
- Enable services
- Deploy an application
- Clone a Git repository
- Update Linux packages
- Reboot servers
- Create directories
- Delete files
- Run shell commands
- Configure cron jobs
- Patch multiple servers

---

# Production Scenarios

Practice explaining how you would:

- Patch 500 Linux servers using Ansible
- Deploy an application to multiple environments
- Roll back a failed deployment
- Restart only affected services after configuration changes
- Use variables for Development, QA, and Production
- Encrypt database passwords using Ansible Vault
- Troubleshoot a failed playbook
- Create a reusable Nginx Role
- Use Tags to patch only Production servers
- Perform a dry run using `--check`

---

# Interview Commands to Remember

```bash
ansible all -m ping

ansible-inventory --list

ansible-playbook site.yml

ansible-playbook site.yml --check

ansible-playbook site.yml --diff

ansible-playbook site.yml --limit web

ansible-playbook site.yml --tags install

ansible-playbook site.yml --skip-tags restart

ansible-playbook site.yml -e "env=prod"

ansible-playbook site.yml -vvv
```

